snippet.textDisplay:
I understand that rich people are rich. They got whatever they need and want in terms of money.

Paparazzi are still way over the line, and a lot of that stuff should be illegal. It's just indecent and disrespectful of human life.

You shouldn't be able to turn that celebrity's down time, when they're specifically trying to live a normal life, into "a show" -- if that's how it goes, they never get a break from "work stuff". If you never get to be "off" from work stuff you'll go crazy. Like I said, it's over the line.

Photographing someone in public, when they happen to be there, sure. That's basically reasonable, up to a point. Pursuing them always, following them everywhere, shouting "hey!" Just to get them to turn toward the camera. It doesn't make sense how it isn't somehow illegal.
